#  вЂў the SHA256SUMS manifest is verified against an RSA-3072 signature made
#    with the maintainer's OFFLINE private key вЂ” so a repo/CDN/TLS compromise
#    alone can't push code (the attacker would also need that key)
#  вЂў SHA-256 integrity check of each file against the (signed) SHA256SUMS
#  вЂў version is taken from the (checksum-verified) script itself, not the
#    standalone VERSION pointer; a pointer/package mismatch is surfaced
#  вЂў syntax-checked (bash -n) before anything is replaced
#  вЂў backs up the current scripts to *.bak (easy rollback)
#  вЂў user-space only (no sudo); preserves THIS install's launch-agent label
#
# Public key for verifying the update manifest's signature. The matching
# private key is held offline by the maintainer (see SIGNING.md) and is never
# in this repo. Verification uses THIS installed script's baked-in key (trust
